{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id43d534e5-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"582"},"text":"§ 582.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Bad debts, losses, and gains with respect to securities held by financial institutions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43d534e6-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Securities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding sections 165(g)(1) and 166(e), subsections (a) and (b) of section 166 (relating to allowance of deduction for bad debts) shall apply in the case of a bank to a debt which is evidenced by a security as defined in section 165(g)(2)(C).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43d534e7-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Worthless stock in affiliated bank","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of section 165(g)(1), where the taxpayer is a bank and owns directly at least 80 percent of each class of stock of another bank, stock in such other bank shall not be treated as a capital asset.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4e8-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Bond, etc., losses and gains of financial institutions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4e9-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" General rule","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this subtitle, in the case of a financial institution referred to in paragraph (2), the sale or exchange of a bond, debenture, note, or certificate or other evidence of indebtedness shall not be considered a sale or exchange of a capital asset. For purposes of the preceding sentence, any regular or residual interest in a REMIC shall be treated as an evidence of indebtedness.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4ea-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Financial institutions to which paragraph (1) applies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4eb-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of paragraph (1), the financial institutions referred to in this paragraph are—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4ec-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any bank (and any corporation which would be a bank except for the fact it is a foreign corporation),","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4ed-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any financial institution referred to in section 591,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4ee-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2/A/iii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any small business investment company operating under the Small Business Investment Act of 1958, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4ef-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2/A/iv"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iv"},"text":"(iv)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any business development corporation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4f0-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Business development corporation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of subparagraph (A), the term “business development corporation” means a corporation which was created by or pursuant to an act of a State legislature for purposes of promoting, maintaining, and assisting the economy and industry within such State on a regional or statewide basis by making loans to be used in trades and businesses which would generally not be made by banks within such region or State in the ordinary course of their business (except on the basis of a partial participation), and which is operated primarily for such purposes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4f1-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a","identifier":"/us/usc/t26/s582/c/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitations on foreign banks","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of a foreign corporation referred to in subparagraph (A)(i), paragraph (1) shall only apply to gains and losses which are effectively connected with the conduct of a banking business in the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id43d7a4f2-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68A/202"},"text":"68A Stat. 202","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/866/tI/s34"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–866, title I, § 34","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1632"},"text":"72 Stat. 1632","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/tIV/s433/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, title IV, § 433(a)","children":[],"tail":", (c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1969","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/83/623"},"text":"83 Stat. 623","children":[],"tail":", 624; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/tX/s1044/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, title X, § 1044(a)","children":[],"tail":", title XIV, § 1402(b)(1)(G), (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-04"},"text":"Oct. 4, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1642"},"text":"90 Stat. 1642","children":[],"tail":", 1732; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dA/tX/s1001/b/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. A, title X, § 1001(b)(6)","children":[],"tail":", (e), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1011"},"text":"98 Stat. 1011","children":[],"tail":", 1012; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/tVI/s671/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, title VI, § 671(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", title IX, § 901(d)(3), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2318"},"text":"100 Stat. 2318","children":[],"tail":", 2379; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647/tI/s1008/d/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647, title I, § 1008(d)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/3439"},"text":"102 Stat. 3439","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/tXI/s11801/a/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, title XI, § 11801(a)(25)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(11), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1388-521"},"text":"104 Stat. 1388–521","children":[],"tail":", 1388–527; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/188/tI/s1621/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–188, title I, § 1621(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-20"},"text":"Aug. 20, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1867"},"text":"110 Stat. 1867","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357/tVIII/s835/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357, title VIII, § 835(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1593"},"text":"118 Stat. 1593","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id43d7a4f3-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id43d7a4f4-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id43d7a4f5-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Small Business Investment Act of 1958, referred to in subsec. (c)(2)(A)(iii), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/699"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–699","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/689"},"text":"72 Stat. 689","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 14B (§ 661 et seq.) of Title 15, Commerce and Trade. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s661"},"text":"section 661 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id43d7a4f6-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357","children":[],"tail":" struck out “, and any regular interest in a FASIT,” before “shall be treated”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/188"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–188","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, and any regular interest in a FASIT,” after “REMIC”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s11801/c/11/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, § 11801(c)(11)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “paragraph (2)” for “paragraph (5)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s11801/a/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, § 11801(a)(25)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(11)(B), redesignated par. (5) as (2) and struck out former par. (2) “Transitional rule for banks” which read as follows: “In the case of a bank, if the net long-term capital gains of the taxable year from sales or exchanges of qualifying securities exceed the net short-term capital losses of the taxable year from such sales or exchanges, such excess shall be considered as gain from the sale of a capital asset held for more than 6 months to the extent it does not exceed the net gain on sales and exchanges described in paragraph (1).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s11801/a/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, § 11801(a)(25)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (3) “Special rules” which read as follows: “For purposes of this subsection—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) The term ‘qualifying security’ means a bond, debenture, note, or certificate or other evidence of indebtedness held by a bank on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-07-11"},"text":"July 11, 1969","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) The amount treated as capital gain or loss from the sale or exchange of a qualifying security shall be determined by multiplying the amount of capital gain or loss from the sale or exchange of such security (determined without regard to this subsection) by a fraction, the numerator of which is the number of days before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-07-12"},"text":"July 12, 1969","children":[],"tail":", that such security was held by the bank, and the denominator of which is the number of days the security was held by the bank.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s11801/a/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, § 11801(a)(25)","children":[],"tail":", struck out par. (4) “Transitional rule for banks” which read as follows: “In the case of a corporation which would be a bank except for the fact that it is a foreign corporation, the net gain, if any, for the taxable year on sales and exchanges described in paragraph (1) shall be considered as gain from the sale or exchange of a capital asset to the extent such net gain does not exceed the portion of any capital loss carryover to such taxable year which is attributable to capital losses on sales or exchanges described in paragraph (1) for a taxable year beginning before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1969-07-12"},"text":"July 12, 1969","children":[],"tail":". For purposes of the preceding sentence, the portion of a net capital loss for a taxable year which is attributable to capital losses on sales or exchanges described in paragraph (1) is the amount of the net capital loss on such sales or exchanges for such taxable year (but not in excess of the net capital loss for such taxable year).”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/s11801/c/11/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, § 11801(c)(11)(B)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (5) as (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–647","children":[],"tail":" substituted “subsections (a) and (b) of section 166” for “subsections (a), (b), and (c) of section 166”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s901/d/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 901(d)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “referred to in paragraph (5)” for “to which section 585, 586, or 593 applies”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s671/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 671(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “For purposes of the preceding sentence, any regular or residual interest in a REMIC shall be treated as an evidence of indebtedness.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s901/d/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 901(d)(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369","children":[],"tail":" substituted “6 months” for “1 year”, applicable to property acquired after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-06-22"},"text":"June 22, 1984","children":[],"tail":", and before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 1988","children":[],"tail":". See Effective Date of 1984 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1976—Subsec. (c)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1402/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1402(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", provided that “9 months” would be changed to “1 year”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1402/b/1/G"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1402(b)(1)(G)","children":[],"tail":", (2), provided that “6 months” would be changed to “9 months” for taxable years beginning in 1977."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/455/s1044/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–455, § 1044(a)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1969—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/s433/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, § 433(c)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Bad debts, losses, and gains with respect to securities held by financial institutions” for “Bad debt and loss deduction with respect to securities held by banks” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/172/s433/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–172, § 433(a)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated existing provisions as par. (1), inserted reference to sections 585, 586 and 593, and added pars. (2) and (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1958—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/866"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–866","children":[],"tail":" struck out “with interest coupons or in registered form,” before “exceed the gains”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id43d7a4f7-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id43d7a4f8-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2004 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/357"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–357","children":[],"tail":" 